Network Byte Order is also known as Big-Endian Byte Order
htons() - convert from Host Byte Order to Network Byte Order short
htonl() - convert from Host Byte Order to Network Byte Order long
ntohs() - convert from Network Byte Order to Host Byte Order short
ntohl() - convert from Network Byte Order to Host Byte Order long

inet_addr() - convert IP string into numbers and dots unsigned long. Returns 
              data in network Byte order.
inet_aton() - convert ascii to network
memset() - set memory area to zeros
perror() - SEE MAN PAGE, and find out how to use it with errno
